                <p><span class="TextRun SCXW15076478 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW15076478 BCX0">Shigeru Mizuki’s <em>Showa </em>series is a semi-autobiographical series of manga that covers not only the major events in Japanese history but also smaller less well-known incidents such as the Tokyo subway sarin attack and an 80s crime ring that threatened to poison candy. </span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<h3 style="margin-top: 0px; font-family: var(--font-base); font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold); letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing); font-size: 1.42383em;"><figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  style="color: var(--text-primary-color); font-family: var(--editor-font-family); font-size: inherit; font-weight: var(--font-weight-normal); outline: 3px solid rgba(var(--color-primary-rgb), 0.55)  !important;" src="https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/10/show1953sketched23_20230705_0008.png" alt="Showa 1953-1989 by Shigeru Mizuki" width="1870" height="2567" sizes="(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 100vw" srcset="https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/10/responsive/show1953sketched23_20230705_0008-xs.png 300w ,https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/10/responsive/show1953sketched23_20230705_0008-sm.png 480w ,https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/10/responsive/show1953sketched23_20230705_0008-md.png 768w"></figure></h3>
<p><span class="EOP SCXW15076478 BCX0" data-ccp-props="{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}"> </span></p>
<h3>Origin</h3>
<p>Tokyo, Japan</p>
<div class="post__iframe"><iframe width="600" height="450" style="border: 0;" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1662975.564103363!2d138.45086767158327!3d35.50429928011098!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x605d1b87f02e57e7%3A0x2e01618b22571b89!2sTokyo%2C%20Japan!5e0!3m2!1sen!2snl!4v1688805877226!5m2!1sen!2snl" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"></iframe></div>
<h3>Shigeru Mizuki and History</h3>
<p>The following page scans from <em>Showa 1926-1939: A History of Japan Vol. 1 </em>show how manga is used to illustrate both the darker and lighter events of Japanese history.</p>
