<h3>Origin</h3>
<div class="post__iframe"><iframe width="600" height="450" style="border: 0;" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d992241.8801554726!2d99.45102123283165!3d13.721789118274629!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x311d6032280d61f3%3A0x10100b25de24820!2sBangkok%2C%20Thailand!5e0!3m2!1sen!2snl!4v1688804171133!5m2!1sen!2snl" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"></iframe></div>
<h3>Book banning in Thailand</h3>
<p>Thailand is notorious for strict rules regarding criticizing the government and/or the monarchy. This <a href="https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/general/2608113/pavins-book-about-monarchy-banned-in-thailand">short article</a> demonstrates the consequences of writing a book that includes any negative comments about both.</p>
<p>Bangkok Post. (2023, July 8). <em>Pavin's book about monarchy banned in Thailand</em>. Retrieved from Bangkok Post: <a href="https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/general/2608113/pavins-book-about-monarchy-banned-in-thailand">https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/general/2608113/pavins-book-about-monarchy-banned-in-thailand</a></p>
