            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/3/sketched23_20230705_0004.png" class="type:primaryImage" alt="Zhuang Zi Speaks: The Music of Nature" /></p>
                <p><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW83311823 BCX0">Zhuang Zi/</span><span class="NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2Themed SCXW83311823 BCX0">Chuang</span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW83311823 BCX0">-Tzu/Zhuangzi/莊子 was an influential writer and philosopher who discussed many topics that both countered and supported Buddhist principles. He was a native of the state of Meng (now located in present-day Henan province) and was born during the Warring States period in China. His ideas focused not only on the characteristics of the Dao, but also the role of nature and human existence</span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW83311823 BCX0">. </span></p>
<h3>Origin</h3>
<p>Henan province, China</p>
<div class="post__iframe"><iframe width="400" height="300" style="border: 0;" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1696141.1634872174!2d112.18618123842566!3d33.86967075351694!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x35d692e354d4df61%3A0x82b2157827a21acb!2sHenan%2C%20China!5e0!3m2!1sen!2snl!4v1688795942195!5m2!1sen!2snl" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"></iframe></div>
<h3>Chinese Through Comics Series excerpts</h3>
<p>Click on a thumbnail to view the full image.</p>
<div class="gallery-wrapper gallery-wrapper--wide"><div class="gallery"  data-is-empty="false" data-translation="Add images" data-columns="3">
<figure class="gallery__item"><a href="https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/3/gallery/zhuangzi23_20230705_0001.png" data-size="1831x2650"><img loading="lazy" src="https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/3/gallery/zhuangzi23_20230705_0001-thumbnail.png" alt="People Neither Live Nor Die" width="768" height="1112"></a>
<figcaption>People Neither Live Nor Die</figcaption>
</figure>
<figure class="gallery__item"><a href="https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/3/gallery/zhuangzi23_20230705_0001b.png" data-size="1795x2609"><img loading="lazy" src="https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/3/gallery/zhuangzi23_20230705_0001b-thumbnail.png" alt="Like a Drifting Boat" width="768" height="1116"></a>
<figcaption>Like a Drifting Boat</figcaption>
</figure>
<figure class="gallery__item"><a href="https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/3/gallery/zhuangzi23_20230705_0001c.png" data-size="1880x2719"><img loading="lazy" src="https://bartob03.github.io/SJSUInfo23710/media/posts/3/gallery/zhuangzi23_20230705_0001c-thumbnail.png" alt="The Horse Lover" width="768" height="1111"></a>
<figcaption>The Horse Lover</figcaption>
</figure>
</div></div>
<h3>Reflect</h3>
<ul>
<li>Do you agree with the ideas presented in the comic strips?</li>
<li><span data-contrast="auto">Do you think Zuang Zi’s ideas in the comic strips are still relevant today?</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}"> </span></li>
<li><span data-contrast="auto">Do you think Zuang Zi's ideas in the comic strips are widely different from Western thinking?</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}"> </span></li>
</ul>
<h3>Explore</h3>
